nowledge. This revision ultimately points to the important contribution of borderland spaces to the fabrication of group identities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 0aHistory (General). 0aHistory of Asia. 0aSocial sciences (General). 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2019z978311066152108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Packagez978311064982640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048536757zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de GruyterzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048536757zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048536757.jpg  a978-3-11-064982-6 Asian Studies Contemporary Collection eBook Package  a978-3-11-066152-1 AUP eBook Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA